+釋持品
+
+Explaining the Upholding Chapter.
+
+---
+二萬菩薩奉命弘經，故名「持品」；重勸八十萬億那由他弘經，故名「勸持品」。
+
+Twenty thousand bodhisattvas receive the command to propagate the sutra, thus it is called the “Upholding Chapter”; again it exhorts eighty thousand koṭis of nayutas to propagate the sutra, thus it is called the “Exhorting to Uphold Chapter.”
+
+---
+問：
+
+Question:
+
+---
+何故爾？
+
+Why is this so?
+
+---
+答：
+
+Answer:
+
+---
+二萬是〈法師品〉初別命之數，故奉旨受持，八十萬億那由他等前無別命，止是通覓。今佛眼視，令其發誓此土通經，通經證驗深重佛意殷勤，是故蒙勸而弘，故有二意也。
+
+The twenty thousand are the number of those separately commanded in the first section of the “Dharma Teacher” chapter, so they receive the Buddha’s order to uphold. The eighty thousand koṭis of nayutas had no separate command before, only a general seeking. Now the Buddha gazes with his eyes and has them vow to propagate the sutra in this land; such propagation proves and manifests the Buddha’s deep and earnest intent. Therefore they are exhorted and propagate — thus there are two meanings.
+
+---
+就文為二：先明受持，後明勸持。初文復三：一、二萬菩薩奉命此土持經，二、五百八千聲聞發誓他國流通，三、諸尼請記。
+
+In the text there are two: first clarifying receiving and upholding, then clarifying exhortation to uphold. The first text again has three: (1) twenty thousand bodhisattvas receive the command to uphold the sutra in this land, (2) five hundred and eight thousand śrāvakas vow to propagate in other lands, (3) the nuns request prediction.
+
+---
+問：
+
+Question:
+
+---
+此諸聲聞已成大士，何故不能此土弘經？
+
+These śrāvakas have already become great bodhisattvas; why can they not propagate the sutra in this land?
+
+---
+答：
+
+Answer:
+
+---
+為引初心始行菩薩未能惡世苦行通經，復欲開於〈安樂行品〉也。
+
+In order to lead beginner bodhisattvas who have just begun practice and cannot yet practice the harsh ascetic propagation in an evil world, and also to open the “Peaceful Practices” chapter.
