+龍師云：「住忍辱地總舉生、法二忍，下別明二忍，『柔和善順』明身業也，『而不卒暴』是口業，『心亦不驚』是意業。此就三業明修生忍。『於諸法無所行』，不行有相也；『而觀如實相』，行空平等也；『亦不行不分別』，不行無相也，有無兩亡會於中道，此三句明修法忍。得是二忍，結為行處。」彼明二忍，未知約何？若三教二忍，全非《法華》之義；若約圓教，不應隔別不融(云云)。
+
+Master Long says: “Dwelling on the ground of patience generally presents the two patiences of beings and dharmas; below it separately clarifies the two patiences. ‘Gentle and compliant’ clarifies body‑karma; ‘and not sudden‑violent’ is mouth‑karma; ‘mind also not startled’ is mind‑karma. This uses the three karmas to clarify cultivating patience toward beings. ‘With respect to dharmas there is nothing to practice’ is not‑practicing of marks; ‘and contemplate the real‑mark’ is practicing emptiness‑equality; ‘also no‑practice, no‑discrimination’ is not‑practicing of no‑marks. With existence and non‑existence both gone and meeting in the middle way, these three sentences clarify cultivating patience toward dharmas. Attaining these two patiences, they are concluded as the practice‑place.” He explains two patiences, but does not know by what they are taken; if by the two patiences of the three teachings, it is entirely not the *Lotus* meaning; if by the Perfect teaching, it should not be separated and not merged (etc.).
